, 
<figureCitation id="1CDC43CDFFEC015062C0F0DC91788BCD" box="[498,521,220,239]" captionStart="Figs 43–54" captionStartId="11.[151,188,1981,2000]" captionTargetBox="[236,1349,522,1969]" captionTargetId="figure-14@11.[236,1352,519,1973]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 43–54. Male head of Taumacera. 43 – T. musaamani (Mohamedsaid, 2010) (Sabah); 44 – T. cervicornis (Baly, 1861) (Sri Lanka); 45 – T. deusta Thunberg, 1814 (Bali); 46 – T. laevipennis (Jacoby, 1886) (Kelantan); 47 – T. insignis (Baly 1864) (Pahang); 48 – T. facialis (Baly, 1886) (Sri Lanka); 49 – T. frontalis Mohamedsaid, 2001 (Perak); 50 – T. indicola nom. nov. (Maharashtra); 51 – T. nigricornis (Baly, 1864) (lateral view, syntype); 52 – T. rufomarginata (Jacoby, 1895) (Java); 53 – T. indica (Jacoby, 1889) (Thailand); 54 – T. variceps (Laboissière, 1933) (Thailand)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4505530" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4505530/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="37">46</figureCitation>
